Vital sign monitoring for home care patients.

18.description:
Heartlytics is an internet-connected medical device and cloud service that make it easier for patients with chronic conditions to measure and report vital signs from home.
Patients can measure various signs like pulse, oxygen saturation, ECG, among others.
This information is stored in their servers to make it available to both patients and treating doctors. Medical staff can check on a patient at any given time, and analyze historic data of the patient.

Heartlytics provides a system of alerts for patients who need to be under constant monitoring. The system can notify the medical staff about an emergency (e.g. a dangerous level drop in pressure) via push notification or sms to quickly get in touch with the patient or even send over an ambulance.
